This paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum matching in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the semi-streaming model, which is a subfield of data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and approximation algorithms, which are common in the sub-fields of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with graph theory, which is a sub-field of Theoretical Computer Science (cs.GT) and Algorithms (cs.AL).
